{
  "text": "where \u03bb is a complex number with |\u03bb| = 1. We take the T-duality transformation along this orbit, which leads to two NS5-branes in flat spacetime [CITATION_1] . The original D2-branes become D1-branes ending on the NS5-branes, while D0-branes change into winding D1-branes in the type IIB side. On the other hand, the D4-brane wrapped on C 4 becomes D3-brane ending on one of the NS5-branes. The brane configuration after the T-dual transformation is summarized in Table 2 . Here x 9 -direction is compactified on a circle for the T-duality transformation. We further perform the S-duality transformation and obtain a D5-D3-F1 system as in Table 3 . This brane configuration can be depicted as in Fig. 1 . The locations direction is R and the distance between D3 and D5 in 9 direction is \u03c0l 0 .",
